  "text": "Neuroseverity scoring was assessed after injury by using a neurobehavioral examination (scoring scale, 7-21) as previously described (Table) . [CITATION_1] Motor score (4 -12) was derived from spontaneous activity, symmetry of limb movements, climbing, balance, and coordination. Sensory score (3-9) was derived from body proprioception, vibrissae, visual, and tactile responses. Sensory tests examined function from both cerebral hemispheres.",
